name: Sepulture
description:
Death became the place where man became better aware of hilmself.

Sepultura is one of the first types of burial, characteristic of the 19th century, composed of drawer and headboard, the function of the inhumation is more important than the sacred elements.

Tomb found in the Municipal Cemetery of Aguá Verde, Curitiba/Brazil - Photogrammetry Scan 

Higor Casagrande - 2022
